One of the most fascinating aspects of society is what we choose to regulate

Ex: we regulate the heck out of medical products, even those posing no risk

Yet we unleash GPT-4 w no regulation despite that it WILL massively impact all of society and every human on earth

Strange.

Am not trying to take a position on AI regulation here but worth remembering that the average senator is 64 years old, the president is 80 years old, the previous president is 76 years old, and the average SCOTUS justice serves until 79 years old. It's not a tech-savvy group.
